-Pick it up!
-(Caitlin sighs)

18:57.834 --> 18:59.667
-Pick it up!
-Caitlin: Okay.

18:59.750 --> 19:01.500
Fraser:
Who the fuck keeps calling you?

19:01.583 --> 19:03.083
-Who is it?
-(beeping)

19:03.166 --> 19:05.417
-Daddy Lt. Col. Poythress?
-(beeping stops)

19:06.917 --> 19:08.083
(Caitlin sighs)

19:09.041 --> 19:11.458
Caitlin:
Does your mom know?

19:11.542 --> 19:13.834
Like, didn't she
give you the money

19:13.917 --> 19:16.083
to buy the tickets?

19:16.959 --> 19:17.917
(sighs)

19:20.166 --> 19:22.917
(groans) Yes, she did,
but she doesn't know.

19:27.208 --> 19:30.792
I use her credit card and
she pretends she doesn't know.

19:30.875 --> 19:33.125
I don't know.
I think she does that... (sighs)

19:33.875 --> 19:36.166
for some form of...

19:36.250 --> 19:37.959
reparation.

19:38.750 --> 19:40.291
For what?

19:42.125 --> 19:43.750
(dog barks)

19:45.500 --> 19:46.875
(sighs)

19:46.959 --> 19:49.959
For everything that
she takes away from me.

19:50.041 --> 19:52.333
Every time that I--
there's someone

19:52.417 --> 19:55.041
that I meet that I like,
she does that.

19:55.125 --> 19:57.792
You know, I've never--
I've never met my father.
I don't know my father.

19:59.458 --> 20:03.667
I've only met my grandfather
three times in my entire life.

20:03.750 --> 20:05.375
(sniffles)

20:05.458 --> 20:07.583
Yeah, that's okay though.

20:07.667 --> 20:09.709
(sniffles) Maybe if I...

20:09.792 --> 20:13.291
you know, got more time
to spend with him,

20:13.375 --> 20:14.959
I'd realize how...

20:16.917 --> 20:19.333
she's so much like him.

20:22.041 --> 20:24.667
And you don't hate her?

20:28.291 --> 20:30.500
I hate her so much.

20:31.792 --> 20:33.417
I hate her with every cell

20:33.500 --> 20:36.667
of my being of my body.
I hate her.

20:38.500 --> 20:40.875
Did she do that with
your New York friend?

20:41.667 --> 20:43.542
What's his name?

20:47.875 --> 20:49.542
(car driving by)

20:52.417 --> 20:54.083
Mark.

20:54.166 --> 20:56.083
Mark.

20:56.166 --> 20:58.542
You two were dating, right?

20:59.792 --> 21:01.000
(sighs)

21:02.375 --> 21:03.709
(sniffles)

21:08.208 --> 21:09.709
No.

21:14.250 --> 21:16.375
Mark, uh...

21:23.875 --> 21:25.542
He... (sighs)

21:27.041 --> 21:29.667
Mark's not...
He's not real.

21:29.750 --> 21:32.291
Doesn't exist.

21:32.375 --> 21:36.083
That is, I-I imagine
myself talking to him.

21:36.166 --> 21:38.083
Like, I'd see him every
single day at school,

21:38.166 --> 21:40.125
and I'd try to convince
myself to go up to him

21:40.208 --> 21:41.542
and introduce myself.

21:41.625 --> 21:44.750
And then when I did,
he'd be thrilled and...

21:44.834 --> 21:46.291
you know.

21:47.250 --> 21:49.250
But I never had the nerve.

21:51.291 --> 21:52.875
Never had the nerve.

21:55.333 --> 21:57.667
Then one time, uh,
I heard him talking

21:57.750 --> 22:00.417
to one of his
friends about how

22:00.500 --> 22:02.166
he saw me staring at him,

22:02.250 --> 22:04.792
and that I was probably,
like, a lunatic or something.

22:08.583 --> 22:10.792
I used to have
a friend like...

22:15.500 --> 22:17.667
somebody like... (sighs)

22:19.583 --> 22:21.417
Never mind. Never mind.

22:25.125 --> 22:26.333
Okay.

22:27.166 --> 22:28.333
Okay?

22:29.041 --> 22:31.083
I mean...

22:31.166 --> 22:34.208
It's crazy, but...

22:34.291 --> 22:36.542
okay. Mark doesn't exist,

22:36.625 --> 22:38.792
Harper doesn't exist.

22:38.875 --> 22:41.250
The two of us, we don't exist.

22:42.291 --> 22:46.291
I mean, it's okay.
I-- Craig doesn't exist.

22:48.083 --> 22:50.458
And... it's okay.

22:51.542 --> 22:54.291
Maybe nothing exists. Like,

22:54.375 --> 22:57.417
Sam. Or the base.

22:57.500 --> 22:59.917
Or our parents.
And that's okay!

23:00.000 --> 23:01.250
(dog barking)

23:01.333 --> 23:03.166
We don't exist!
Do you hear that?!

23:03.250 --> 23:05.917
-Nope! Can't hear that
'cause we don't exist!
-(dogs barking)

23:06.000 --> 23:08.250
-Fraser: So fuck off!
-Yeah, fuck off!

23:08.333 --> 23:09.542
(laughing)
We don't exist!

